<p><strong>Chapter 1 - A breakthrough in the Treatment of Mood Disorders</strong></p>

<p>Depression is the number one public health problem in the world.</p>

<p>Cognitive Therapy (CT) is a mood modification that you can learn on your own :
    1. Rapid Symptomatic Improvement 
    2. Understanding : clear explanation of your actual mood.
    3. Self-control 
    4. Prevention and Personnal Growth : reassessment.</p>

<p>You create those feelings by the dialogue you are having with yourself.</p>

<p>Cognitive distortions :</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>ALL-OR-NOTHING THINKING : Black and White</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>OVERGENERALIZATION : single negative event = never-ending pattern of defeat</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>MENTAL FILTER : one negative event is making everything dark (drop on ink)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>DISQUALIFYING THE POSITIVE : they-dont-count experiences</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>JUMPING TO CONCLUSION : negative interpretation over sth (Mind reading  &amp; Fortune Teller Error)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>MAGNIFICATION OR MINI : exageration of failures vs minimisation of strenghts</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>EMOTIONAL REASONING : your emotions = reality (procra)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>SHOULDY : guilt</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>LABELING &amp; MISLABELING : cf OVER - labeling yourself the wrong way</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>PERSONALIZATION : responsabilities to others (teachers)</p>
  </li>
</ol>

