<p><strong>Chapter 9 - Sadness is not depression</strong></p>

<p>sadness : negative event involving loss or disappointment in an undistorted way
depression : illness that always results from thoughts</p>

<p>stress -&gt;reactive depression -&gt;endogenous</p>

<p>Loss of life: constant worth and productivity
Loss of limb: thinking pattern -&gt;focus on what you can do
Loss of job: DCT -&gt; temporary disease process
Loss of loved one: personnalization -&gt;misconceptions
Sadness without suffering: ‚ÄúYou can love. You can care.‚Äù</p>

