<p><strong>Chapter 13 - Your work is not your worth</strong></p>

<p>‚ÄúMy worth as a human being is proportional to what I have achieved in my life‚Äù -&gt; FAKE NEWS</p>

<p>Less productivity = you are not good ? -&gt; FAKE NEWS</p>

<p>standards of the marketplace?</p>

<p>-&gt; Success does not guarantee happiness -&gt; your thoughts are the key to your mood</p>

<p>happiness and great achievements have no necessary connection</p>

<p>defining achievement = worth? vs worth = achievement ?</p>

<p>METHO = operationalization</p>

<p>you are the one who‚Äôs telling yourself your lack of status or achievement</p>

<p>Four Paths to self esteem:</p>

<ol>
  <li>human worth is just an abstraction -&gt; it does not exist -&gt; it is self defeating -&gt; dump it in the trash, you‚Äôve got nothing to lose</li>
  <li>set realistic goals for yourself and work toward them -&gt; acknowledge that everyone has one ‚Äúunit of worth‚Äù from the time they are born until the time they die</li>
  <li>recognize that there is only one way you can lose a sense of self worth -&gt; persecuting yourself with unreasonable, illogical negative thoughts</li>
  <li>self esteem can be viewed as your decision to treat yourself like a beloved friend -&gt; VIP -&gt; self love and self respect</li>
</ol>

<p>Escape from the achievement trap:</p>

<p>achievement comes only through success in your career ? -&gt; FAKE NEWS</p>

<p>remember to talk back -&gt; DCT</p>

<p>being productive can be very satisfying and enjoyable but its NOT NECESSARY in order to be HAPPY</p>

