<p><strong>Chapter 14 - Dare to be average - Ways to overcome perfectionism</strong></p>

<p>Perfection is the man ultimate illusion -&gt; it simply does not exist in the universe</p>

<p>averageness is another kind of illusion</p>

<p>the harder you strive for perfection, the worse your disappointment</p>

<p>If you are a perfectionist you are guaranteed to be a loser in whatever you do</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Make a list of advantages and disadvantages of being perf.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>experiment -&gt; lowering</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>the antiperfectionism sheet -&gt; amount of satisfaction = break the illusory connection between perfection and satisfaction</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>look around you -&gt; <em>you are guaranteed to be a sure loser if you maintain a standard for evaluating your performance that you can‚Äôt ever meet</em></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>confrontation with fear -&gt; do things less perfectly -&gt; ‚Äúcompulsive slowness‚Äù -&gt; ‚Äúresponse prevention‚Äù = you refuse to give in into perf</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>vertical arrow  to find silent assumptions - going to let go your perfectionism  = expose yourself to an initial unpleasantness</p>

    <p>if you endure the discomfort -&gt; you will conquer your fears because they are ultimately based on illusions -&gt; accept your humanness</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>develop a process orientation -&gt; focus on processes rather than outcomes -&gt; mostly disarming technique = I will try get many rejections as possible -&gt; I was successfully rejected -&gt; this bring me one important step to my goal</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>assuming responsibility for your life -&gt; setting strict time limits (POMODORO)</p>
